FBIS3-59919 "jptac001___94045" JPRS-TAC-94-001 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Arms Control 18 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA UKRAINE Kiev Dismantles SS-24 Nuclear Missiles Announcement Made 20 December AU2012173193 Paris AFP in English 1722 GMT 20 Dec 93 AU2012173193 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Kiev, Dec 20 (AFP) -- Ukraine is to dismantle almost half of the 46 SS-24 nuclear missiles in its nuclear arsenal inherited from the former Soviet Union, Deputy Prime Minister Valery Shmarov said Monday. He said Ukraine would dismantle 20 of the 46 strategic missiles by the end of this month. The decision comes only days after last week's meeting of top Ukrainian, Russian and U.S. officials. Until now Ukraine has refused to give up the weapons without security guarantees from the United States.
